VIS 2128: Assignment 2

Joy Linyue Zhang

9/14/2022

This interactive map intends to explore the relationship between the distribution of bike facilities (Blue Bike stations and Bike Lanes) and the population of the census tracts in Boston. According to the map, Blue Bike stations and Bike Lanes are not distributed in accordance with the census tracts population. Census tracts with a greater population do not necessarily have a high concentration of Blue Bike stations and Bike Lanes.

When you hover over a census tract, you can check its ID. When you click the green lines or the blue dots, you can see the name of the Bike Lanes and the Blue Bike Stations.

The map may help planners or government officials reflect on whether the distribution of the bike facilities meets residents needs. This map may also offer some insights for further studies on the accessibility and equity of the Blue Bike stations and bike lanes.

Data Sources: All data is abttained from Bostons Open Data Portal

  • 2020 Census data for the City of Boston

  • 2020 Census Tract Boundry of Boston

  • Blue Bike Station in Boston (updated in 2022)

  • Bike Network of Boston (updated in 2022)
